  "text": "We uploaded in the database a data set of ∼1.5 GB (gigabytes) that contains the 3D coordinates of reference points of a simulated model of the human genome [CITATION_1] . All these positions were indexed in the database using the spatial index (the description of PostGIS's spatial index can be found at http://revenant.ca/www/postgis/workshop/ indexing.html). Then, we measured the speed of reaching the data through the Java application using the PostGIS JDBC driver, and the influence of the size of the output (results of query) on the processing time.",
